<TITLE> Rights body looks to HC to prevent food adulteration </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, January 14 (bdnews24.com)A human right group filed a writ petition with the High Court Wednesday seeking a direction upon the government to constitute an advisory counsel to prevent food adulteration. "It is the right of the citizens to get pure food. But adulterated food is spread all over the market, which causes serious threat to health and life of the citizens," said the petition. A HC bench of justices ABM Khairul Haque and Md Abdul Hai may hear the public interest litigation writ, filed by advocate Manzil Morshed of Human Rights and Peace for Bangladesh, on Thursday. Secretary of the ministry of health and secretary of the ministry of food were made respondents in the petition. After filing the petition, advocate Manzil Morshed told bdnews24.com that a direction is necessary to constitute an advisory counsel as per the Pure Food Ordinance, 1959 to formulate necessary policy to prevent adulteration in food. Manzil Morshed himself will move the petition. bdnews24.
